		"Id": "mechdef_broadside_BS-12D",
		"Name": "Broadside",
		"Details": "Developed by Iroquois Machinery Limited as their first entry into true BattleMech production, the Broadside has been met with heavy skepticism by Davion MechWarriors. However, after an impressive showing from a cadet in the 1st Conroe Training Battalion against a Kuritan Atlas, the Broadside is coming to be more broadly accepted. The design is built around a 300-rated fusion engine with Endo-Steel bones and Triple Strength Myomer for extra power. Despite what its Davion roots would indicate, the BS-12D does not carry a battery of autocannons, instead opting more of a fire-support design with three Thunderbolt-10s and two Thunderbolt-15s. 8 tons of CASE II protected ammunition keeps the guns firing in any situation while a small handful of ER lasers (both Medium and Small) ensure the design has some direct-fire support should it become necessary.",
		"Icon": "uixTxrIcon_broadside"
	},
